n To create your own Filters, follow this procedure: \n   Create a new Filter \n In the Model Browser, go to  Data  /  Entities , under the package folder of your application, right-click on the Entity for which you want to create the Filter and select  New  /  Filter : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2de4bf9131f1ac29c6a4c2466e8cce45064ac674.png]\nDescription: The image presents a UI interface from a Model Browser within a software application, likely for managing data configurations or structures. The left pane displays a hierarchical tree view under \u0022myapplication,\u0022 encompassing sections such as \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 with subcategories like \u0022Constants,\u0022 \u0022Data Structures,\u0022 \u0022Database Data Types,\u0022 and \u0022Entities.\u0022 Under \u0022Entities,\u0022 there are items listed such as \u0022_Orgam General Interfaces,\u0022 \u0022_spreadsheet,\u0022 \u0022_system,\u0022 \u0022Dimensions,\u0022 \u0022myapplication,\u0022 with sub-items \u0022Priority,\u0022 \u0022Status,\u0022 and \u0022Task.\u0022 A right-click context menu is visible, displaying options under \u0022New,\u0022 including \u0022New Group,\u0022 \u0022Repeat New,\u0022 \u0022Actions,\u0022 \u0022Convert To,\u0022 \u0022Move To Package,\u0022 along with the selections \u0022Expand All,\u0022 \u0022Edit item,\u0022 \u0022Delete,\u0022 \u0022Execute,\u0022 and \u0022Find Dependencies.\u0022 The interface facilitates data management tasks such as filtering and editing configurations.\n\n\n  \n In the Filter details, name the Filter (e.g.,): \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/83f18b28819e3c4f1594c2ab0d032f82f8b565c5.png]\nDescription: This image displays a user interface for an entity filter in a software application, likely related to data management or development. The top section shows the filter title \u0022TasksAfterDeadline,\u0022 with a button for adding filters. Below, an information panel presents the following fields: \u0022Id\u0022 with the value e4b0dc31-0e3-4219-a8b0-a745a18f6944, \u0022ItemType\u0022 listed as EntityFilter, \u0022PackageName\u0022 as myapplication, \u0022RelativeFilePath\u0022 detailing myapplication\\Data\\Entity\\myapplication\\Task.origam, and \u0022SchemaItemType\u0022 as Origam.Schema.EntityModel.EntityFilter. In the schema item details, \u0022Ancestors\u0022 is marked as False, \u0022Inheritable\u0022 is also set to False, and the \u0022Name\u0022 is reiterated as TasksAfterDeadline. The apparent purpose of this interface is to define and manage filters for data-related tasks in a specified application context.\n\n\n  \n Save it. \n   Add Function(s) \n In the Model Browser, right-click on the Filter you just created and select  New  /  Function Call : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/95292e627bb4345ad4cacd96e6cb7c01113addac.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface from a software application, specifically a Model Browser. In the hierarchy, it includes sections labeled \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022Entities,\u0022 with a focus on \u0022Data Structures\u0022 and \u0022Database Data Types.\u0022 Under \u0022Entities,\u0022 there are items such as \u0022Priority,\u0022 \u0022Status,\u0022 \u0022Task,\u0022 and \u0022_Ancestors.\u0022 A context menu labeled \u0022Function Call\u0022 is visible, offering options such as \u0022New Group,\u0022 \u0022Repeat New,\u0022 and \u0022Convert To.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to manage and organize data structures and entities within the application, likely for development or data management tasks.\n\n\n  \n   Configure Function(s) \n In the Function Call properties, provide the  Name  and select the  Function  you want to use: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5278f4f9484ab39d3b0774355f0c5c0406b27189.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a data modeling tool, specifically focusing on a function call labeled \u0022GreatThanOrEqual.\u0022 The visible sections include an \u0022Info\u0022 part detailing the Id, ItemType, PackageName, RelativeFilePath, and SchemaItemType. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:51:33"},"vector":[-0.020900486,-0.03116093,-0.05993485,0.0072694663,-0.0013239922,-0.05797047,0.024197286,0.004188105,-0.01207855,0.00924679,0.0017204994,-0.016822785,-0.006787664,0.028401421,0.0004017189,-0.014058513,0.0027829234,0.0022837562,-0.009426357,-0.0049874787,-0.007632015,-0.029402437,0.017213378,-0.016173575,-0.018373499,0.038301587,0.00473646,-0.024330948,0.0057840436,-0.00054505124,0.022456666,-0.07693628,-0.0023247597,-0.027856559,-0.0010262545,-0.020080999,0.011161577,0.009404896,-0.040170867,0.015451412,-0.009863907,0.007891233,-0.018904489,0.005375179,0.008173252,-0.034956947,-0.007337157,-0.0021234327,-0.014478193,-0.06070386,-0.035707857,-0.01088195,0.0021393113,-0.044854876,0.051811233,0.04183254,-0.049207304,-0.02537719,-0.027408507,0.023967307,-0.0224026,-0.020541616,0.03952559,-0.021269431,0.021581247,0.0038459513,-0.028604088,-0.010310291,-0.0079045445,-0.033027846,0.0006987189,0.025732765,-0.073708996,-0.026448967,-0.032230698,-0.0047754575,-0.0056404243,0.00071051094,-0.047138125,0.034138136,-0.01998295,-0.017785849,-0.0034753755,-0.012856412,0.004963567,0.009496737,-0.0071403515,0.09344737,0.037468735,0.0019064656,-0.04709355,-0.0035817444,0.07944,-0.053023785,-0.020402648,0.0074009467,-0.01923327,-0.016600676,0.003909432,0.008700702,-0.0074144104,-0.022764934,-0.031681556,-0.00911274,-0.027341342,-0.033670284,0.01325629,-0.044376288,-0.040575106,-0.028075052,-0.0047170743,0.030897085,0.005667325,0.023137225,0.0038816656,0.008527841,0.019796705,-0.0045586578,0.005860508,0.013651043,0.0075941924,0.021019302,0.09286109,-0.018950377,0.0017901349,0.0010464138,-0.03080